Common Household Pests We Handle

Browse by category and see quick signs, risks, and the typical treatment approach.

12

Pests covered

Eco

Family-safe focus

Plan

Prevent return

Ants

Persistent trails and repeat activity around food and moisture.

INSECTS
Signs: Visible trails, small piles of soil, and activity near sinks or pantries.
Risks: Food contamination and rapid colony growth if the nest isn’t addressed.
Treatment: Targeted baiting + perimeter barriers and entry-point sealing.

Spiders

Webbing and sightings in corners, basements, and garages.

INSECTS
Signs: Webs, egg sacs, and increased sightings around lights or clutter.
Risks: Most are harmless, but bites are possible and indicate other pests nearby.
Treatment: Reduce harborage + targeted treatment and prevention around entry points.

Cockroaches

Hardy indoor pests that thrive in warmth, moisture, and crumbs.

INSECTS
Signs: Pepper-like droppings, egg cases, musty odor, and nighttime activity.
Risks: Can spread bacteria and trigger allergies/asthma.
Treatment: Gel baits + growth regulators, sanitation guidance, and exclusion.

Crickets

Noisy at night and often attracted to moisture and warm spaces.

INSECTS
Signs: Chirping, sightings in basements/garages, and minor fabric/paper damage.
Risks: Nuisance infestations and contamination in storage areas.
Treatment: Moisture reduction + perimeter treatments and sealing gaps.

Mice

Small, fast breeders that squeeze through tiny openings.

RODENTS
Signs: Droppings, gnaw marks, scratching sounds, and greasy rub marks.
Risks: Disease exposure, food contamination, and electrical/fire hazards.
Treatment: Trapping + exclusion work to close entry points and prevent return.

Rats

Stronger, more destructive rodents often linked to outdoor access.

RODENTS
Signs: Larger droppings, burrows, gnaw damage, and frequent sightings.
Risks: Serious contamination risks and structural/property damage.
Treatment: Baiting/trapping strategy + exterior exclusion and habitat changes.

Earwigs

Often show up after rain—drawn to damp areas around foundations.

INSECTS
Signs: Sightings in bathrooms, kitchens, and near baseboards or mulch.
Risks: Mostly nuisance, but can indicate moisture problems.
Treatment: Moisture control + targeted exterior treatments and sealing.

Silverfish

Paper-loving pests that prefer dark, humid rooms and storage.

INSECTS
Signs: Damage to books/paper, shed skins, and sightings in bathrooms or basements.
Risks: Damage to stored items and ongoing humidity-related issues.
Treatment: Humidity reduction + crack/crevice treatment and prevention.

Moths

Clothing and pantry moths can quietly damage stored items.

INSECTS
Signs: Holes in fabrics, webbing in corners, or larvae near stored foods.
Risks: Damage to clothing, carpets, and pantry goods.
Treatment: Targeted treatment + storage/cleaning guidance and monitoring traps.

Centipedes

Fast, nocturnal hunters that appear where other bugs thrive.

INSECTS
Signs: Sightings at night in basements, bathrooms, and damp areas.
Risks: Possible bites and a sign of underlying moisture/pest activity.
Treatment: Moisture reduction + perimeter control and sealing.

Millipedes

Often wander indoors when conditions outside are too wet or dry.

INSECTS
Signs: Slow-moving pests near doors/windows; curled bodies if they die indoors.
Risks: Nuisance and moisture-related entry pathways.
Treatment: Exterior habitat adjustments + sealing and perimeter protection.

Termites

Wood-destroying pests that can cause expensive hidden damage.

WOOD
Signs: Mud tubes, hollow-sounding wood, shed wings, or swarmers seasonally.
Risks: Structural damage if left untreated.
Treatment: Inspection + targeted treatment plan (baiting or localized solutions).
